One of my largest next decade and beyond plays is fintech. Of which I think $SOFI has an incredible runway to take off. It's floor is being a buyout target for a $JPM or $GS type that wants to integrate their hyper growth customer base into legacy banking. I think it's at fair value right now just under $20 a share. 

&amp;#x200B;

$FRSH is also on my watch list. Use the software for work and it just works. Really great product, regular joe schmoes can use their API Integrations to optimize work flows, etc. It won't be salesforce but it can cut into that market if you ask me. Valuation prior to upcoming earnings is a little rich, but mid to high 30's would be a solid entry. 

&amp;#x200B;

&amp;#x200B;

$PSFE is a massive risk massive reward situation. Absolute beat down stock with heavy institutional investment in the 7$ range. It's a payment processing platform that some consider a proxy to the gambling sector. Lots of debt from M&amp;A but the price targets are juicy. (Trading around 8$ right now with many targets of 15). 

&amp;#x200B;

Stripe (Whenever it IPO's next year). Can you tell I like fintech? lol
